name: Wand of Sun
description: An alder wand charged with light magic. Releases a small sun at the enemy. The most powerful weapon in the game.

name: Skull Rod
description: An alder wand charged with dark magic.  Releases skulls and bones at the enemy.

name: Fireball Wand
description: An alder wand charged with powerful fire magic.  Launches a fireball at the enemy.

name: Eagle Wand
description: An alder wand charged with earth magic. Releases an angry eagle at the enemy.

name: Mace of Kiros
description: This weapon was carried by the winner of the Arena fights of 50, the knight Kiros Ironhead. Despite the heavy weight of the cast iron core, for some unknown reason, this mace is easy to hold in the hand.

name: Dragon Slayer
description: With this sword, Sir Ailenrod slew the dragon Garas. The sword has double damage against dragons.

name: Axe of Bone Richard
description: Axe of the legendary warrior Richard. Once Richard participated in the war on the side of the first king, he was able to conquer many settlements until he was brutally killed by a traitor in a duel, who gave him a special alcoholic elixir of lethargy. She took his axe.

name: Bone Richard's Axe
description: According to legend, the legendary warrior Bone Richard lost his life and his favorite axe. Then he found this axe and went to take revenge on everyone and everything in the Cursed Mist.

name: Zino's Rod of Power
description: A powerful rod, probably made from an alloy of gold and terbian ore, turns any mage into a true master of magic. According to the seller, this rod was once used by a certain Zino, during the time of his family's power.

name: Spear of the Sea Titans
description: A magical spear enchanted with water magic and deals both physical and water damage to the enemy with each attack.

name: Falder's Hammer
description: The legendary hammer with which the bodyguard of the dwarven king Gahard broke over 1000 skulls.

name: Destroyer
description: A very sharp and heavy axe that emits a strange red glow...

name: Kiros's Plate
description: This plate was forged for the third winner of the arena fights, the knight Kiros Ironhead.

name: Kiros's Cloak
description: A powerful cloak made of thick, unknown material worn by the knight Kiros Ironhead.

name: Kiros' Necklace
description: An enchanted necklace that provides great defense against physical attacks. Belongs to the knight Kiros Ironhead.

name: Kiros' Gauntlets
description: Steel gauntlets from the armor of the knight Kiros. He once won the arena of champions in them.

name: Kiros' Steel Belt
description: The legendary steel belt of the knight Kiros, forged for him by the Order of the Guardians of the White Mountains.

name: Iron Boots of Kiros
description: Legendary steel boots of the knight Kiros, the great warrior and winner of the third battles in the Arena. They have mental defense properties.

name: Kiros' Steel Helmet
description: Legendary helmet of the knight Kiros. Forged by the order of the guardians of the White Mountains from an alloy of Terbian and iron ore.

name: Steel Shield of Kiros
description: Legendary shield of the knight Kiros. Consists of high-strength steel smelted in the high-temperature forge of the order of the guardians of the White Mountains.

name: Garas Skin Cuirass
description: This leather cuirass was made from the skin of the legendary dragon Garas, who terrorized settlements in the northern Land of Giants. It has outstanding fire resistance.

name: Garas Skin Cap
description: Cap made from the skin of the red dragon Garas. It has good fire resistance and protection from magic.

name: Cloak of Garas's Skin
description: Cloak decorated with the skin of Garas, the dragon who burned settlements in the north of the Land of Giants.

name: Ailenrod's Necklace
description: This gold necklace was given to Sir Ailenrod for defeating the dragon Garas. It is probably the original.

name: Gloves of Garas's Leather
description: Expensive and exquisite leather gloves decorated with the skin of the red dragon Garas.

name: Belt of Garas
description: A leather belt made from the skin of the legendary dragon Garas. This dragon once terrorized the lands south of the Royal Castle.

name: Boots of Garas
description: Leather boots decorated with the skin of the legendary dragon Garas. Highly resistant to water.

name: Shield of Garas
description: A bronze shield depicting the legendary dragon Garas, who for many years ravaged settlements south of the Adarian Ridge.

name: Chainmail of Bone Richard
description: This chainmail was worn by the legendary warrior Richard, who after death, already being a skeleton, killed thousands of brave men in the swamps of the Cursed Mist.

name: Robe of Bone Richard
description: Cursed robe of the fallen warrior Richard, who wore it as a skeleton. The robe grants a powerful influx of magic.

name: Amulet of Richard of Bones
description: A discreet Amulet worn by the legendary warrior of the creation era, Richard of Bones, gained immense magical power after his death...

name: Gloves of Bone Richard
description: Gloves of the legendary warrior Richard, who died during the war of creation. According to legend, after death, Richard's skeleton went to the Cursed Mist, where he began to take revenge on the living for the fate that fate had written for him...

name: Bone Richard's Belt
description: A leather belt with the skull of the legendary warrior Richard. This belt was made after his death, and therefore is not of great value.

name: Bone Richard's Treads
description: Chainmail treads worn by the legendary warrior Richard of Bones. Provides increased protection against physical attacks.

name: Helmet of Bone Richard
description: This helmet is made of very strong iron and provides excellent protection against slashing weapons. It once belonged to the legendary warrior Richard, who fought in the early years of the kingdom.

name: Shield of Bone Richard
description: A wooden shield with a skull. This shield belonged to the legendary warrior of the first king, Richard, nicknamed Bone. The shield is made from the magical wood of the trees of the Singing Thicket. It has excellent protection against elemental magic.
